104
00:08:07,564 --> 00:08:11,334
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Little by little, we're seein'
some definite results.</b></font>

105
00:08:11,334 --> 00:08:15,004
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Compared to the old Takumi,
he's a completely different guy.</b></font>

106
00:08:15,004 --> 00:08:18,844
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Takumi's developing at a
frighteningly fast pace, is he?</b></font>

107
00:08:18,844 --> 00:08:21,744
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I guess. But...</b></font>

108
00:08:27,114 --> 00:08:30,024
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>He's still got a long way to go.</b></font>

109
00:08:34,564 --> 00:08:38,724
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Incredible... Something is different</i>
<i>about this eighth round!</i></b></font>

110
00:08:45,134 --> 00:08:50,044
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I never placed much importance</i>
<i>on racing lines for street races.</i></b></font>

111
00:08:50,044 --> 00:08:56,284
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>All I think about is using my tires to</i>
<i>the fullest and having a good race.</i></b></font>

112
00:08:56,284 --> 00:09:00,384
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Through practicing the single-handed steer,</i>
<i>I noticed that if you fully utilize your tires,</i></b></font>

113
00:09:00,384 --> 00:09:04,484
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>then no matter what line you take,</i>
<i>it won't make much difference in racing time.</i></b></font>

114
00:09:06,424 --> 00:09:08,224
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Following that thinking,</i></b></font>

115
00:09:08,224 --> 00:09:14,434
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>the resulting line is that which</i>
<i>most effectively uses the tires!</i></b></font>

116
00:09:14,434 --> 00:09:17,404
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>That's precisely what the "record line"is!</i></b></font>

117
00:09:18,504 --> 00:09:21,504
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>To me, the ideal racing line</i>
<i>is not to be sought.</i></b></font>

118
00:09:21,504 --> 00:09:24,514
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>It is nothing more than a result!</i></b></font>

119
00:09:24,514 --> 00:09:27,134
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>What I'm seeing is so incredible!</i></b></font>

120
00:09:42,424 --> 00:09:44,494
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Part of being fast on the mountain pass</b></font>

121
00:09:44,494 --> 00:09:47,804
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>is being able to enter
corners without hesitation.</b></font>

122
00:09:47,804 --> 00:09:52,504
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>How well you know the course
is a vital element of this.</b></font>

123
00:09:52,504 --> 00:09:57,614
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It is also a basic principle in the
theory of high-speed public racing.</b></font>

124
00:09:57,614 --> 00:09:59,314
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It is for this reason</b></font>

125
00:09:59,314 --> 00:10:01,314
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>that practice is emphasized
during D's expeditions.</b></font>

126
00:10:01,314 --> 00:10:05,154
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>So... local drivers who've raced
the course for a long time</b></font>

127
00:10:05,154 --> 00:10:06,554
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>have an advantage?</b></font>

128
00:10:06,554 --> 00:10:11,854
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Correct. Especially during races
between two drivers of great skill,</b></font>

129
00:10:11,854 --> 00:10:14,894
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>knowledge of the course will
ultimately become a weapon.</b></font>

130
00:10:14,894 --> 00:10:18,234
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Then how will this race turn out?</b></font>

131
00:10:18,234 --> 00:10:22,534
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It will be a battle of endurance.
He who can't endure will lose.</b></font>

